ApiExceptionHandler - Class in com.jdroid.javaweb.api
Renders a response with a RESTful Error representation based on the error format discussed in Spring MVC Rest Exception Handling Best Practices.

At a high-level, this implementation functions as follows: The HTTP Response's Status Code will be set to the ApiError's status value. The ApiError instance is presented to a configured HttpMessageConverter to allow transforming the ApiError instance into an object potentially more suitable for rendering as the HTTP response body. The HttpMessageConverters are consulted (in iteration order) with this object result for rendering.
